@startuml
title Horizon Bank process-architecture decomposition and traceability

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ranksep 12
skinparam nodesep 18
skinparam ArrowColor #334155
skinparam ArrowFontColor #1E293B
skinparam ArrowFontSize 11
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #F8FAFC
  BorderColor #334155
  FontColor #0F172A
  RoundCorner 8
}

rectangle "CATALOGUE LEVEL\nCustomer and party management\nProcess family" as FAMILY #E0F2FE
rectangle "END-TO-END LEVEL\nEstablish customer relationship\nProcess" as PROCESS #DBEAFE
rectangle "SELECTED SUBPROCESS LEVEL\n1  Capture application\n2  Verify identity and screen\n3  Resolve referral [exception path]\n4  Create party and account records\n5  Confirm usable service" as DECOMP #F8FAFC

rectangle "ACCOUNTABILITY\nOnboarding process owner" as OWNER #F3E8FF
rectangle "OUTCOME\nUsable banking relationship" as OUTCOME #DCFCE7
rectangle "CONTROLS\nIdentity evidence | Screening evidence" as CONTROLS #FEE2E2
rectangle "MEASURES\nElapsed time | Straight-through processing\nReferral rate | Control failures" as MEASURES #FEF3C7
rectangle "CAPABILITIES EXERCISED\nCustomer Onboarding | Identity Verification\nFinancial Crime Screening\nParty Management | Account Opening" as CAPS #E0E7FF
rectangle "REFERENCE RESPONSIBILITIES\nCandidate BIAN Service Domains and interactions\nBIAN 14.0 logical reference\nCandidate, partial and many-to-many" as BIAN #F1F5F9
rectangle "SELECTED DETAIL\nBPMN collaboration for behaviour and referral exception\nNot a full-bank process diagram" as BPMN #ECFDF5

FAMILY -down-> PROCESS : contains
OWNER -left-> PROCESS : is accountable for
PROCESS -down-> DECOMP : decomposes to
DECOMP -down-> OUTCOME : produces
OUTCOME -down-> CONTROLS : is constrained by
CONTROLS -down-> MEASURES : is measured by
MEASURES -down-> CAPS : exercises
CAPS -down-> BIAN : is informed by
BIAN -down-> BPMN : details selected behaviour

note bottom
  Selected Horizon Bank onboarding excerpt.
  Process, capability, BIAN responsibility and implementation are not equivalent.
end note
@enduml
